org.jpws.pwslib.order

Class FilterRecordList

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.jpws.pwslib.order.OrderedRecordList
      • org.jpws.pwslib.order.FilterRecordList
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    PwsFileListener, OrderedListListener

    public abstract class FilterRecordList
extends OrderedRecordList
implements OrderedListListener
    This is an abstract class for a filter class that resides above an OrderedRecordList L. The filter class is an OrderedListListener and performs the selection of a subset of the items contained in L. The filter class performs widely as an OrderedRecordList itself and thus is capable of substituting the role of OrderedRecordList for its listeners. It is, however, notably not a PwsFileListener (although it formally say so)!

    The filtering function is performed over a callback function acceptEntry(PwsRecord). This method is to be implemented by a concrete filter class.

    Since:
    0-3-0

      • loadDatabase

        public void loadDatabase(PwsRecordList list,
                         long expireScope)
        Description copied from class: OrderedRecordList
        Loads a list of PwsRecords from a PwsRecordList object by discarding any previous content. If this object is bound to a PwsFile, the parameter list must also be a PwsFile and have an identical resource file (persistent file). If this object is not bound to a database, this method does, however, not lead to bondage, regardless of the instance type of list.

        This method makes this object listen to the parameter record list for content change events.

        Overrides:
        loadDatabase in class OrderedRecordList
        Parameters:
        list - database to be loaded
        expireScope - time span in milliseconds for expire-soon status of records; 0 for ignore

      • insertItem

        public void insertItem(DefaultRecordWrapper wrapper)

        WARNING!! Applying this when this list has bondage may lead to de-synchronization of list and database. This method does not insert a record into the database.
